race.comment: Competitive. MASTER OF DISGUISE (7) is third-up and ready to fire off solid efforts in town. Has been kept up to the mark with a Canberra trial placing and will carry just 52kgs this grade with the 3kg claim atop. Has the blinkers on for the first time and the Seib barn is flying. VELLA FOX (4) presents off an Open win at Canberra and that stacks right up. He has won 3/4 second up and keeps the in-form Boudvillain. He can race forward and should get every chance. YAM (6) will be fitter again and he posted a strong relative number at Bendigo last time. He has claims on the 9-day return. CANNY HELL (2) was on speed missing a whisker in a Wagga Open. The 2kg claim is handy but the outside gate requires a good ride. Has claims regardless.
